text: 100 years ago today the Great Kanto Earthquake struck Yokohama, Japan (neighbor city of Tokyo) killing 140,000 people. The 7.9 magnitude earthquake demolished hundreds of thousands of homes, left 1.5 million people homeless & started fires that burned 45% of Tokyo. A fire whirl was triggered as a result of the earthquake which incinerated 38,000 people in downtown Tokyo. A tsunami was also triggered which destroyed even more homes and killed more people. The damage was so bad, officials even contemplated moving the capital Lesson 1: Despite the turmoil it seems like our country is in, we have a lot to be thankful for. Lesson 2: Let's continue to pressure our politcians to help the people of Maui who suffered a similar disaster.
